<node TEXT="Certainly not all of my projects have 100% test coverage (in" ID="ID_1754684017" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="fact, as you read this, sandman might not have 100% coverage" ID="ID_212052921" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="anymore). Getting to 100% was a useful exercise, though. It" ID="ID_32833204" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="exposed bugs and opportunities for refactoring I wouldn&apos;t have" ID="ID_482448676" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="otherwise noticed." ID="ID_912897798" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="Since, as for the tests themselves, test coverage reports can" ID="ID_1055335311" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="be generated automatically as part of your continuous" ID="ID_1499743196" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="integration. If you choose to do so, displaying a badge" ID="ID_1610315046" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="showing your current test coverage adds a bit of transparency" ID="ID_1395630921" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="to your project (and high numbers can sometimes encourage" ID="ID_1134600199" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="others to contribute)." ID="ID_1279025560" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="virtualenv and virtualenvwrapper" ID="ID_1412208522" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876">
<node TEXT="Ian Bicking&apos;s virtualenv tool has become the de-facto standard" ID="ID_1250314905" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="mechanism for isolating Python environments. Its purpose is" ID="ID_178395562" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="simple: if you have a number of Python projects on a single" ID="ID_1066215951" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="machine, each with different dependencies (perhaps with" ID="ID_1135480088" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="dependencies on different versions of the same package), managing" ID="ID_1881545292" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="the dependencies in a single Python installation is nigh" ID="ID_1410202810" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="impossible." ID="ID_203202955" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="virtualenv creates &quot;virtual&quot; Python installations, each with their" ID="ID_1776914012" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="own, segregated, site-packages. distribute and pip are also" ID="ID_1846774120" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="installed in such a way that pip install correctly installs" ID="ID_1792358546" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="packages to the virtualenv rather than the system Python" ID="ID_1379768121" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="installation. Switching back and forth between your virtualenv is" ID="ID_174563034" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="a one-command process." ID="ID_391839981" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="A separate tool, Doug Hellmann&apos;s virtualenvwrapper, makes creating" ID="ID_27501356" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="and managing multiple virtualenvs easier. Let&apos;s go ahead and" ID="ID_1672793980" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="install both now:" ID="ID_40333663" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="$ pip install `virtualenvwrapper` ...  Successfully installed" ID="ID_1953939131" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="`virtualenvwrapper` `virtualenv` `virtualenv`-clone stevedore" ID="ID_534237885" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="Cleaning up..." ID="ID_1948269038" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="As you can see, the latter has a dependency on the former, so" ID="ID_768049010" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="simply installing virtualenvwrapper is sufficient. Note that if" ID="ID_729791777" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="you&apos;re using Python 3, PEP-405, which gives Python native support" ID="ID_227782523" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="for virtual environments through the venv package and pyvenv" ID="ID_433147124" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="command, was implemented in Python 3.3. You should use that" ID="ID_1883432426" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="instead of the tools mentioned above." ID="ID_51464452" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="Once you&apos;ve installed virtualenvwrapper, you&apos;ll need to add a line" ID="ID_1648697214" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="to your .zhsrc file (or .bashrc file for bash users):" ID="ID_952320252" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="$ echo &quot;source /usr/local/bin/virtualenvwrapper.sh&quot; &gt;&gt; ~/.zshrc" ID="ID_1593227417" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="This adds a number of useful commands to your shell (remember to" ID="ID_1566019753" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="source your .zshrc to actually make them available for the first" ID="ID_1280986820" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="time). While you can create a virtualenv directly with the" ID="ID_552043862" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="mkvirtualenv command, creating a &quot;project&quot; using mkproject" ID="ID_484679462" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="[OPTIONS] DEST_DIR is usually more useful. Since we have an" ID="ID_1002181919" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="existing project, however, we&apos;ll simply create a new virtualenv" ID="ID_155923791" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="for our project. We can do this with a simple command:" ID="ID_1544448172" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="$ mkvirtualenv ossproject" ID="ID_718482680" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="New python executable in ossproject/bin/python Installing" ID="ID_1067944012" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="setuptools............done.  Installing pip...............done." ID="ID_1121590633" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="(ossproject)$" ID="ID_1540853535" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="You&apos;ll notice your shell prompt is now prepended by the name of" ID="ID_1825408590" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="your virtualenv (which I called &quot;ossproject&quot;, but obviously you" ID="ID_1938230280" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="can use whatever name you&apos;d like). Now anything installed via pip" ID="ID_620064768" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="install is installed to the site-packages of your virtualenv." ID="ID_1816331372" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="To stop working on your project and switch back to the system" ID="ID_855446301" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="installation, use the deactivate command. You should see the" ID="ID_1691225420" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="virtualenv name that was prepended to your shell prompt" ID="ID_1279833384" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="disappear. To resume work on your project, run $ workon &lt;project" ID="ID_659991280" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="name&gt; and you&apos;ll be back in your virtualenv." ID="ID_1692592588" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="Aside from simply creating the virtualenv for your project, you&apos;ll" ID="ID_1141278500" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="use it to do one more thing: generate your requirements.txt" ID="ID_663483893" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="file. pip is capable of installing all of project&apos;s dependencies" ID="ID_1047617603" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="by using a requirements file and the -r flag. To create this file," ID="ID_1048068537" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="run the following command within your virtualenv (once your code" ID="ID_1723454481" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="is working with the virtualenv, that is):" ID="ID_471197665" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="(ossproject)$ pip freeze &gt; requirements.txt" ID="ID_1318255403" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="You&apos;ll get a nice list of all of the requirements for your" ID="ID_265689447" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="project, which can later be used by the setup.py file to list your" ID="ID_1059686403" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="dependencies. One note here: I often change the &apos;==&apos; to &apos;&gt;=&apos; in" ID="ID_1514127040" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="requirements.txt to say &quot;any version of this package after the one" ID="ID_936728444" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="I&apos;m working on.&quot; Whether or not you should/need to do this is" ID="ID_57060743" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="project specific, but I just thought I&apos;d point it out." ID="ID_1369563487" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="Commit requirements.txt to your git repo. In addition, you can now" ID="ID_1289688726" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="add the packages listed there as the value for the" ID="ID_1030145007" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="install_requirements argument to distutils.setup in" ID="ID_331933543" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="setup.py. Doing that now will ensure that, when we later upload" ID="ID_1899694114" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="the package to PyPI. It can be pip installed with automatically" ID="ID_1168007442" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
<node TEXT="resolved dependencies." ID="ID_302267147" CREATED="1406792949876" MODIFIED="1406792949876"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Documentation with Sphinx" ID="ID_102500343" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="Sphinx is a tool by the pocoo folks. It&apos;s used to" ID="ID_653516063" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="generate the Python&apos;s official documentation and the" ID="ID_1182036139" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="documentation for almost all other popular Python" ID="ID_1322318143" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="packages. It was written with idea of making" ID="ID_691452282" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="auto-generation of HTML documentation from Python code" ID="ID_1253784420" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="as easy as possible." ID="ID_1034640214" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Let the tool do the work" ID="ID_24125969" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="Sphinx has no implicit knowledge of Python programs" ID="ID_118837702" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="and how to extract documentation from them. It can" ID="ID_1730719163" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="only translate reStructured Text files, which means a" ID="ID_1117668977" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="reStructured Text version of your code&apos;s documentation" ID="ID_1652404023" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="needs to be available for Sphinx to do its work. But" ID="ID_74693196" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="maintaining a reStructured Text version of all of your" ID="ID_258707695" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT=".py files (minus the actual body of functions and" ID="ID_1666432551" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="classes) is clearly not doable." ID="ID_471054902" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Luckily, Sphinx has a javadoc-like extension, called" ID="ID_902366816" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="autodoc, which is able to extracted reStructured Text" ID="ID_150373521" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="from your code&apos;s docstrings. To be able to fully" ID="ID_148235884" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="utilize the power of Sphinx and autodoc, you&apos;ll need" ID="ID_1853896033" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="to format your docstrings in a particular manner. In" ID="ID_1737405504" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="particular, you should make use of Sphinx&apos;s Python" ID="ID_1558916989" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="directives. Here&apos;s an example of a function documented" ID="ID_254572436" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="using reStructured Text directives, making the" ID="ID_561784408" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="resulting HTML documentation much nicer:" ID="ID_563969340" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="def _validate(cls, method, resource=None):" ID="ID_204003565" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="&quot;&quot;&quot;Return ``True`` if the the given *cls* supports the HTTP *method* found" ID="ID_374424552" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="on the incoming HTTP request." ID="ID_304988451" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT=":param cls: class associated with the request&apos;s endpoint" ID="ID_67774919" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT=":type cls: :class:`sandman.model.Model` instance" ID="ID_94567446" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT=":param string method: HTTP method of incoming request" ID="ID_71553426" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT=":param resource: *cls* instance associated with the request" ID="ID_1207118271" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT=":type resource: :class:`sandman.model.Model` or None" ID="ID_1301178435" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT=":rtype: bool" ID="ID_1645175217" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="&quot;&quot;&quot;" ID="ID_263172948" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="if not method in cls.__methods__:" ID="ID_1912614603" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="return False" ID="ID_1891764366" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="class_validator_name = &apos;validate_&apos; + method" ID="ID_1525225101" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="if hasattr(cls, class_validator_name):" ID="ID_1517743707" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="class_validator = getattr(cls, class_validator_name)" ID="ID_503171806" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="return class_validator(resource)" ID="ID_1647979835" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="return True" ID="ID_737479396" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Documentation becomes a bit more work, but the payoff" ID="ID_1821860786" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="is worth it for your users. Good, accessible" ID="ID_1885156568" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="documentation sets a usable project apart from a" ID="ID_1518391473" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="frustrating one." ID="ID_1411140707" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Sphinx&apos;s autodoc extension gives you access to a" ID="ID_1124504205" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="number of directives that automatically generate" ID="ID_595621195" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="documentation from your docstrings." ID="ID_1881862678" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Installation" ID="ID_852151088" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="Be sure to install Sphinx in your virtualenv, since" ID="ID_1997165608" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="documentation will be a versioned artifact in your" ID="ID_230514010" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="project. Different versions of Sphinx may generate" ID="ID_1698873222" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="different HTML output. By installing in your" ID="ID_428568740" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="virtualenv, you can &quot;upgrade&quot; your documentation in a" ID="ID_1110077839" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="controlled manner." ID="ID_503695806" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="We&apos;ll be keeping our documentation in the docs" ID="ID_1761077743" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="directory and the generated documentation in the" ID="ID_141143830" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="docs/generated directory. To auto-generate" ID="ID_210340873" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="reStructured Text documentation files from your" ID="ID_105501666" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="docstrings, run the following command in your" ID="ID_585833611" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="project&apos;s root directory:" ID="ID_987954386" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="$ sphinx-apidoc -F -o docs &lt;package name&gt;" ID="ID_390324770" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="This will create a docs directory with a number of" ID="ID_1007727406" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="documentation files. In addition, it creates a conf.py" ID="ID_863973883" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="file, which is responsible for configuration of your" ID="ID_1076349993" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="documentation. You&apos;ll also see a Makefile, handy for" ID="ID_596586594" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="building HTML documentation in one command (make" ID="ID_308961533" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="html)." ID="ID_882029218" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Before you actually generate your documentation, be" ID="ID_768533585" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="sure you&apos;ve installed your package locally ($ python" ID="ID_600747288" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="setup.py develop is the easiest way to keep it up to" ID="ID_1542142666" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="date, though you can use pip as well) or else" ID="ID_1152749902" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="sphinx-apidoc won&apos;t be able to find your package." ID="ID_1676461552" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Configuration: conf.py" ID="ID_828760427" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="The conf.py file that was created controls many" ID="ID_690550031" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="aspects of the documentation that&apos;s generated. It&apos;s" ID="ID_1330098233" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="well documented itself, so I&apos;ll briefly touch on just" ID="ID_495861937" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="two items." ID="ID_386144645" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="version and release" ID="ID_935124733" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="First, make sure to keep your version and release" ID="ID_943642351" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="values up-to-date. Those numbers will be displayed as" ID="ID_86351478" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="part of the generated documentation, so you don&apos;t want" ID="ID_1871992111" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="them to drift from the actual values." ID="ID_1853672560" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="The easiest way to keep your version up to date, in" ID="ID_1541689249" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="both your documentation and setup.py file, is to have" ID="ID_1368322121" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="it read from your package&apos;s __version__ attribute. I" ID="ID_794935600" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="&quot;borrowed&quot; the following conf.py code for sandman from" ID="ID_1454565245" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Flask&apos;s conf.py:" ID="ID_1976966092" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
