<node TEXT="Standardized Testing With Tox" ID="ID_1694310689" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877">
<node TEXT="One issue all Python project maintainers face is" ID="ID_1210396192" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="compatibility. If your goal is to support both Python 2.x and" ID="ID_1016123915" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="Python 3.x (and, if you currently only support Python 2.x, it" ID="ID_103570202" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="should be), how do you make sure your project actually works" ID="ID_1397914767" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="against all the versions you say you support? After all, when" ID="ID_57694315" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="you run your tests, you&apos;re only testing the specific" ID="ID_1365444104" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="interpreter version used to run the tests. It&apos;s quite possible" ID="ID_931343898" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="that a change you made works fine in Python 2.7.5 but breaks" ID="ID_1218097979" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="in 2.6 and 3.3." ID="ID_13416599" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="Luckily, there&apos;s a tool dedicated to solving this exact" ID="ID_551350443" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="problem. tox provides &quot;standardized testing in Python,&quot; and it" ID="ID_1771625165" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="goes beyond merely running your tests with more than one" ID="ID_1655086764" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="version of the interpreter. It creates a fully sandboxed" ID="ID_48544816" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="environment in which your package and its requirements are" ID="ID_854715491" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="installed and tested. If you made a change that works fine" ID="ID_1869582294" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="when tested directly but the change inadvertently broke your" ID="ID_1752654359" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="installation, you&apos;ll discover that with tox." ID="ID_1774821509" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="tox is configured via an .ini file: tox.ini. It&apos;s a very" ID="ID_1630545211" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="simple file to set up. Here&apos;s a minimal tox.ini file taken" ID="ID_1892568300" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="from the tox documentation:" ID="ID_1871333321" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="# content of: tox.ini , put in same dir as setup.py" ID="ID_1045243955" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="[tox]" ID="ID_1279582368" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="envlist = py26,py27" ID="ID_786676849" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="[testenv]" ID="ID_178766781" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="deps=pytest       # install pytest in the venvs" ID="ID_386719565" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="commands=py.test  # or &apos;nosetests&apos; or ..." ID="ID_1136541503" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="By setting py26 and py27 in the envlist, tox knows that it" ID="ID_112119117" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="should run your tests against those versions of the" ID="ID_968177701" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="interpreter. There are about a dozen &quot;default&quot; environments" ID="ID_1907620621" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="that tox supports out of the box, including jython and" ID="ID_1585799870" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="pypy. tox makes testing against different versions and" ID="ID_318169606" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="configurations it would be a crime not to support multiple" ID="ID_282946234" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="versions, if only to get to use such an awesome tool." ID="ID_1977008992" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="deps is a list of dependencies for your package. You can even" ID="ID_930947291" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="tell tox to install all or some of your dependencies from an" ID="ID_1760961428" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="alternate PyPI URL. Clearly, quite a bit of thought and work" ID="ID_1136763069" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="has gone into the project." ID="ID_142473531" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="Actually running your all of your tests against all of your" ID="ID_1719655082" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="environments now takes four keystrokes:" ID="ID_922624732" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="$ tox" ID="ID_397383745" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="A more complicated setup" ID="ID_1892003239" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877">
<node TEXT="My book, &quot;Writing Idiomatic Python&quot;, is actually written as a" ID="ID_188287529" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="series of Python modules and docstrings. This is done to make" ID="ID_869435136" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="sure all the code samples work as intended. As part of my" ID="ID_1154147388" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="build process, I run tox to make sure the code in any new" ID="ID_973237884" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="idioms works correctly. I also occasionally check my test" ID="ID_1606023293" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="coverage to make sure there are no idioms inadvertently being" ID="ID_1103996996" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="skipped during testing. As such, my tox.ini is a bit more" ID="ID_1722956735" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
<node TEXT="complicated than the one above. Take a look:" ID="ID_1383883283" CREATED="1406792949877" MODIFIED="1406792949877"/>
