</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="PyPI" ID="ID_1827360913" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="PyPI, the Python Package Index (formerly known as &quot;the" ID="ID_258300793" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Cheeseshop&quot;) is a central database of publicly available" ID="ID_765097185" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Python packages. PyPI is where your project&apos;s releases &quot;live.&quot;" ID="ID_406808570" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Once your package (and its associate meta-data) has been" ID="ID_1679292697" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="uploaded to PyPI, others can download and install it using pip" ID="ID_1520321554" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="or easy_install. This point bears repeating: even if your" ID="ID_1574271283" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="project is available on GitHub, it&apos;s not until a release is" ID="ID_1911443377" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="uploaded to PyPI that your project is useful. Sure, someone" ID="ID_1126309898" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="could clone your git repo and manually install it directly," ID="ID_11234612" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="but far more people just want to pip install it." ID="ID_970081445" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="One last step" ID="ID_1047648776" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="If you&apos;ve completed all of the steps in the previous sections," ID="ID_1496858435" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="you&apos;re likely anxious to bundle up your package, upload it to" ID="ID_1682990168" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="PyPI, and make it available to the world!" ID="ID_941601163" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Before you do so, however, there&apos;s a helpful tool called" ID="ID_995461224" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="cheesecake that is helpful to run as the last step before" ID="ID_1752470828" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="distributing your package. It analyzes your package and" ID="ID_1869971792" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="assigns &quot;scores&quot; in a number of categories. It measures how" ID="ID_1039648988" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="easy/correct packaging and installing your package is, the" ID="ID_1044671855" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="quality of the code, and the quality and quantity of your" ID="ID_965553297" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="documentation." ID="ID_1025190238" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="As a coarse measure of &quot;readiness&quot;, cheesecake is great for" ID="ID_1299787851" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="sanity checking. You&apos;ll quickly see if there&apos;s an issue with" ID="ID_298405437" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="your setup.py file or if you forgot to document a file. I" ID="ID_874183805" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="recommend running it before each upload to PyPI, not just the" ID="ID_46187827" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="first one." ID="ID_42644567" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Initial upload" ID="ID_426653681" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="Now that you&apos;ve confirmed your code isn&apos;t crap and won&apos;t break" ID="ID_664224890" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="when people try to install it, let&apos;s get your package on PyPI!" ID="ID_1066046351" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="You&apos;ll be interacting with PyPI through setuptools and the" ID="ID_10585123" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="setup.py script. If this is the first time this particular" ID="ID_381427349" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="package is being uploaded to PyPI, you&apos;ll first need to" ID="ID_1042702807" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="register it:" ID="ID_193652666" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="$ python setup.py register" ID="ID_359381121" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Note: if you don&apos;t yet have a free PyPI account, you&apos;ll need" ID="ID_896536830" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="to make one now to be able to register the package. After" ID="ID_1780327791" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="you&apos;ve followed register prompts, you&apos;re ready to create your" ID="ID_239908794" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="distributable package and upload it to PyPI:" ID="ID_1166177612" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="$ python setup.py sdist upload" ID="ID_1028731366" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="The command above builds a source distribution (sdist) and" ID="ID_1194283364" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="uploads it to PyPI. If your package isn&apos;t pure Python (that" ID="ID_1608362608" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="is, you have binaries that need to be built), you&apos;ll need to" ID="ID_634413175" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="do a binary distribution. See the setuptools documentation for" ID="ID_566664398" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="more info." ID="ID_964013945" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Releases and version numbers" ID="ID_1513872138" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="PyPI uses a release version model to decide which version of" ID="ID_60166006" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="your package should be available by default. After the initial" ID="ID_1861593682" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="upload, you&apos;ll need to create a release with a new version" ID="ID_1111770090" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="number each time you want your updated package to be made" ID="ID_72298667" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="available on PyPI. Managing your version number can actually" ID="ID_1590996363" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="be a fairly complex topic, so much so that there&apos;s a PEP for" ID="ID_1945094462" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="it: PEP 440 -- Version Identification and Dependency" ID="ID_1238710444" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Specification. I&apos;d definitely suggest following the guidelines" ID="ID_334795159" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="in PEP 440 (obviously), but if you choose to use a different" ID="ID_1381229378" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="versioning scheme, the version used in setup.py must be" ID="ID_1263411156" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="&quot;higher&quot; than what&apos;s currently on PyPI for PyPI to consider" ID="ID_314439475" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="the package a new version." ID="ID_1506536328" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="Workflow" ID="ID_777789497" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="After uploading your first release to PyPI, the basic" ID="ID_1519466828" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="workflow is this:" ID="ID_1193812016" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878">
<node TEXT="Do some work on your package (i.e. fix bugs, add" ID="ID_630938639" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="features, etc) Make sure the tests pass &quot;Freeze&quot; your" ID="ID_1592633181" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="code by creating a release branch in git-flow Update" ID="ID_1692736492" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="the __version__ number in your package&apos;s __init__.py" ID="ID_102687224" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="file Run python setup.py sdist upload to upload the" ID="ID_1730804186" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
<node TEXT="new version of your package to PyPI" ID="ID_1388582472" CREATED="1406792949878" MODIFIED="1406792949878"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Users depend on you to release frequently enough to get" ID="ID_157509481" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="bug fixes out. As long as you&apos;re properly managing your" ID="ID_739199229" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="version numbers, there is no such thing as releasing &quot;too" ID="ID_672747129" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="frequently.&quot; Remember: your users aren&apos;t manually" ID="ID_952205390" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="maintaining the different versions of every Python package" ID="ID_1436615445" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="they have installed." ID="ID_1495057771" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Continuous Integration with TravisCI" ID="ID_1488900467" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="Continuous Integration refers to the process of continuously" ID="ID_475177805" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="integrating all changes for a project (rather than periodic" ID="ID_1268357887" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="bulk updates). For our purposes, it means that each time we" ID="ID_333640120" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="push a commit to GitHub our tests run, telling us if the" ID="ID_1331880556" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="commit broke something. As you can imagine, this is an" ID="ID_1148220454" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="incredibly valuable practice. There&apos;s no more &quot;forgetting to" ID="ID_1337295261" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="run the tests&quot; before committing/pushing. If you push a commit" ID="ID_1205610676" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="that breaks the tests, you&apos;ll get an email telling you so." ID="ID_405724073" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="TravisCI is a service that makes continuous integration for" ID="ID_289449558" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="GitHub projects embarrassingly easy. Head over there and" ID="ID_1931753826" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="create an account if you don&apos;t yet have one. Once you&apos;re done," ID="ID_899635946" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="we&apos;ll need to create one simple file before we&apos;re swimming in" ID="ID_1247367538" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="CI goodness." ID="ID_1524220487" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="Configuration via .travis.yml" ID="ID_1540691269" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="Individual projects on TravisCI are configured via a file," ID="ID_1790799919" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT=".travis.yml, in the project&apos;s root directory. Briefly, we need" ID="ID_1564526493" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="to tell Travis:" ID="ID_1354095182" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="What language our project is written in" ID="ID_30426728" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="What version of that language it uses" ID="ID_1764353890" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="What commands are used to install it" ID="ID_1289778921" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="What commands are used to run the project&apos;s tests" ID="ID_1672572405" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Doing so is quite straightforward. Here are the contents of" ID="ID_474336763" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="the .travis.yml file from sandman:" ID="ID_376172660" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="language: python" ID="ID_1107475424" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="python:" ID="ID_153007667" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="- &quot;2.7&quot;" ID="ID_1059914815" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="install:" ID="ID_792039324" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="- &quot;pip install -r requirements.txt --use-mirrors&quot;" ID="ID_121184031" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="- &quot;pip install coverage&quot;" ID="ID_340827577" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="- &quot;pip install coveralls&quot;" ID="ID_1370493534" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="script:" ID="ID_1847172744" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="- &quot;coverage run --source=sandman setup.py test&quot;" ID="ID_1424842502" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="after_success:" ID="ID_1851361097" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="coveralls" ID="ID_1213538383" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="After listing the language and version, we tell Travis how to" ID="ID_353817095" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="install our package. Under install:, make sure you have the" ID="ID_504078077" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="line:" ID="ID_1845374336" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="- &quot;pip install -r requirements.txt --use-mirrors&quot;" ID="ID_779660605" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="This pip installs our projects requirements (and uses PyPI" ID="ID_910186215" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="mirrors if necessary). The other two lines in install are" ID="ID_1744833266" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="specific to sandman. It&apos;s using an additional service" ID="ID_640136752" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="(coveralls.io) to continuously monitor test case coverage, but" ID="ID_1596523863" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="that&apos;s not necessary for all projects." ID="ID_453329470" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="script: lists the command needed to run the project&apos;s" ID="ID_805301550" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="tests. Again, sandman is doing some extra stuff. All your" ID="ID_770157579" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="project needs is python setup.py test. And the after_success" ID="ID_492127017" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="portion can be dropped all together." ID="ID_1348250685" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="Once you&apos;ve committed this file and activated your project&apos;s" ID="ID_1052975611" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="repo in TravisCI, push to GitHub. In a few moments, you should" ID="ID_1941214265" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="see a build kick off on TravisCI based on your most recent" ID="ID_1630063178" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="commit. If all is successful, you build will be &quot;green&quot; and" ID="ID_1244239872" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="the status page will show that the build passed. You&apos;ll be" ID="ID_1746248304" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="able to see the history of all of your project&apos;s builds at any" ID="ID_622211745" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="time. This is especially useful for multi-developer projects," ID="ID_645339196" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="where the history page can be used to see how often a" ID="ID_1787370814" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="particular developer breaks the build..." ID="ID_395858287" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="You should also receive an email letting you know the build" ID="ID_768912400" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="was successful. Though you can probably configure it" ID="ID_1074114056" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="otherwise, you&apos;ll get emails only when the build is broken or" ID="ID_12988907" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="fixed, but not if a commit has the same outcome as the build" ID="ID_1614817236" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="that preceded it. This is incredibly useful, as your not" ID="ID_986360654" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="inundated by useless &quot;the build passed!&quot; emails but are still" ID="ID_278104642" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="alerted when something changes." ID="ID_1158620085" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="ReadTheDocs for Continuous Documentation Integration" ID="ID_595046555" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="While PyPI has an official documentation site (pythonhosted.org)," ID="ID_626872787" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="ReadTheDocs provides a better experience. Why? ReadTheDocs has" ID="ID_203897759" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="great integration with GitHub. Once you register on ReadTheDocs," ID="ID_1384128888" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="you&apos;ll see all of your GitHub repos. Select the appropriate repo," ID="ID_1849573683" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="do some minor configuration, and your documentation will be" ID="ID_1214325484" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="automatically regenerated after each commit to GitHub." ID="ID_1059245496" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="Configuring your project should be a straightforward affair. There" ID="ID_1127073598" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="are a few things to remember, though. Here&apos;s a list of" ID="ID_786413550" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="configuration fields and the values you should use which might not" ID="ID_1801398873" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="be immediately obvious:" ID="ID_1053760294" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="Repo: https://github.com/github_username/project_name.git" ID="ID_1135560071" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879" LINK="https://github.com/github_username/project_name.git"/>
<node TEXT="Default Branch: develop" ID="ID_1059983712" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="Default Version: latest" ID="ID_977678147" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="Python configuration file: (leave blank)" ID="ID_1004133079" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="Use virtualenv: (checked)" ID="ID_1024713776" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="Requirements file: requirements.txt" ID="ID_1729484114" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
<node TEXT="Documentation Type: Sphinx HTML" ID="ID_334335260" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879"/>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Don&apos;t Repeat Yourself" ID="ID_1819822812" CREATED="1406792949879" MODIFIED="1406792949879">
<node TEXT="Now that you&apos;ve done all that hard work to open-source an existing" ID="ID_233811390" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="code base, you likely don&apos;t want to have to repeat it all when" ID="ID_1065771649" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="starting a new project. Luckily, you don&apos;t have to. Audrey Roy&apos;s" ID="ID_879946291" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="Cookiecutter tool (I&apos;ve linked to the Python version, though there" ID="ID_592684570" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="are versions for numerous languages in the main repo)." ID="ID_939909656" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="Cookiecutter is a command line tool that automates the process of" ID="ID_380629104" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="starting a project in a way that makes doing the stuff discussed" ID="ID_1384460158" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="in this article easy. Daniel Greenfeld (@pydanny) wrote a great" ID="ID_21071843" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="blog post about it and how it relates to the practices discussed" ID="ID_967206147" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="in this article. You should check it out: Cookiecutter: Project" ID="ID_187318332" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="Templates Made Easy." ID="ID_937035545" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Conclusion" ID="ID_1701910438" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881">
<node TEXT="We&apos;ve now covered all of the commands, tools, and services that go" ID="ID_182026934" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="into open sourcing an existing Python package. Sure, you could" ID="ID_736726238" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="have just thrown it on GitHub and said, &quot;install it yourself,&quot; but" ID="ID_1107110873" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="no one would have. And you wouldn&apos;t really have Open Source" ID="ID_109650622" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="Software; you&apos;d simply have &quot;free code.&quot;" ID="ID_41442981" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="What&apos;s more, you likely never would have attracted outside" ID="ID_603459611" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="contributors to your project. By setting up your project in the" ID="ID_465403607" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="manner outlined here, you&apos;ve created an easy to maintain Python" ID="ID_1072236076" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="package that encourages both use and contribution. And that, after" ID="ID_1122751918" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
<node TEXT="all, is the true spirit of Open Source Software, is it not?" ID="ID_553808141" CREATED="1406792949881" MODIFIED="1406792949881"/>
</node>
</node>
